TJ Nowak Supply Company is a 70 year old business, based in Fort Wayne, Indiana providing technical services and industrial supplies to a regional customer base located in Northern Indiana, Southern Michigan and Western Ohio.

That company is TJ Nowak Supply.

   Our company has several divisions each designed to allow our customers to enjoy multiple services provided by one supply partner. As a gold and silver dealer, CMIGS' mission is to guide and direct investors into the precious metal that best fits their investment goals, while offering the lowest prices available. We will recommend only those precious metals investments that we believe will provide you the biggest profits, not the ones that provide us the biggest profits. organization_seo_description: Strobels Supply is a leading industrial supply distribution & liquid paint application company carrying 3M, Sika, Axalta, & other top-rated brands. Order online today!
organization_short_description:
Strobels Supply, formerly known as Strobels Welding Inc., was a family business started in the 1940's specializing in industrial distribution in the rail car industry. In 2003 the welding business was sold and became Strobels Supply Inc. under new management and new ownership.In 2010 Strobels Supply Inc. began to expand on their distribution parameters by opening up to the entire world with a retail website. We purchase materials from some of the most renowned manufacturers' in the world such as 3M, Axalta (formerly DuPont), Sika, Loctite, Dormer, Starrett, and many more!
In 2012 Strobels Supply Inc., with its' many years of experience and understanding of the transportation industry, began its' production side of the business. Representing Axalta (formerly DuPont) paints for years, we began this division with the thought of offering the customer a one stop shop. We can provide the paint as well as apply the paint to the meet or exceed customer specifications on all metals, composites, or fiberglass. 
In 2014 Strobels Supply Inc. launched its' new division, the Flooring division. Our flooring product is an impermeable paint sprayed on seamless coating for floors. We are certified installers of the flooring, as well.
Under new management and ownership, Strobels developed a worldwide presence, and has increased employment over the last 3 years from 5 employees to 25. We now service rail car companies across the country and in Canada, and have expanded on that to serve every facet of the transportation industry. Strobels has also expanded our services to multiple manufacturing industries such as airports, telecommunications, and oil and gas.

FireSeal is a Swedish company that develops and sells systems for fire sealing.

The company was founded over 40 years ago to carry out a mission from the Swedish Government – to develop a system for fire sealing Sweden's nuclear power plants. Building on this pioneering work, FireSeal has developed a successful business in two sectors: marine and offshore in Asia and the U.S., as well as the construction sector, primarily in Sweden and Norway, where FireSeal is the market leader in soft fire sealing solutions.

FireSeal is a part of Bergman & Beving. Bergman & Beving own and develop companies that develop and market strong brands to professional users in industry and construction – primarily in the Nordics, Baltic States and Poland. Our vision is to be the market leader in northern Europe. Bergman & Beving must be the place where successful product companies are able to take the next step towards becoming the leading brands in their categories. Currently, the group has 15 brands, approximately 1,000 employees and an annual turnover of approximately SEK 3.8 billion. Bergman & Beving was founded in 1906 and is listed on Nasdaq Stockholm. organization_seo_description: Business owners, are you looking to expand your product selection? Sign up for a FREE account and check out our vast selection of over 1200+ import and domestic toys.
organization_short_description:
A Little About Us:
Our roots start from a small annexed backroom in San Gabriel, California (USA). We started out originally as a B2B company providing local retailers with import titles. Within a year, we relocated to a 1,000 square foot retail front serving the heart of San Gabriel Valley. It was during these golden years that we specialized in all import games/hardware.

By 2010, we have relocated to a 10,000 sq. foot facility just a few miles south of Old Town Pasadena.

Today, we have grown to distribute not only import video games, but also an extremely robust line of licensed toy merchandise from world-famous brands. With deep vendor relationships throughout the world, we are able to globally deliver and distribute within time and under budget to our wholesale clients and direct end-consumers.

With a combined total of over 50 years of retail and distribution experience, we are continuously scouting the world over for the most popular and innovative products available. We are your direct source for import toys and games.

Who We Are:
We care about your sales as much as you do. Our business is truly run like a family and we treat our clients like family too. If you buy too much of the wrong item, we'll stop you and tell you to spend your money where it might be more fruitful. 

If you buy too little when you should be buying more, we'll ask you to buy more so you can take advantage of a season/lifestyle of a product. We are not interested in selling you items that aren't a fit for your store. After all, we want you to be lifetime clients.

What We Will Do For You:
What has excited us is that we've learned that we're in the business of helping you create the most beautiful and desirable toy environments that deliver unbelievable amounts of happiness to your clients.

organization_short_description:
At American Mills, Inc., we create distinctive, and quality products for the home, with interesting designs ranging from simple to simply perfect!!  

Spalding Knitting Mills was founded by Robert Paine Shapard in 1921. It began in Griffin, Georgia with the initial products being children's knit socks. From that beginning, American Throwing Company was developed by R.P. Shapard, Jr. in 1938.

Today American Mills, Inc. produces and imports products including: decorative pillows, indoor/outdoor cushions, table linens, indoor/outdoor rugs, pet beds, and plush animals. We currently employ 150 people and have over three hundred thousand square feet of manufacturing and warehouse space in Griffin, Georgia. Our product lines are shown in our permanent showroom at 7 West in New York.

Cushion Pros, a custom cushion division of American Mills, Inc. was launched by company owners Bill and Alisa Shapard in August, 2012. Cushion Pros offers hundreds of superior fabrics by Sunbrella and Robert Allen. Our unique Custom Cushion Designer tool allows you to easily sort your fabric by color, pattern, material or brand. Then choose the shape, enter your size, and select the fill material for your custom cushion.

"As a fourth generation family owned business, we have a long history of commitment to excellence.
We have been providing quality products for over 75 years!" - Bill Shapard

East Coast Grocery Sales Management, Brokerage and Consulting specializing in Natural and Organic food.

Some will say that BROKERS SUCK!!!!!

This is not a grocery industry wide opinion, but it is something we hear from time to time. Often, it's more subtle. X charges too much, why add the extra expense? I did all the work anyway, they don't do much….

People that say this often need a broker the most. 😀

We could go on and on. We have not dealt with this too much personally, but it is something we have to be aware of.

So, how is SMB Sales & Marketing different? Spoiler alert, pragmatically, we're not. We perform the same functions as other brokers.

Why go with us then?

We bring the passion!
Using knowledge, hustle & adaptability to get you on shelf. Because all we care about is getting you on shelf.

We do want to work for you! We don't want to kill you with fees. We want to be honest about the challenges you will face. We want to be in it with you!

We won't succeed unless you succeed!

We can be a broker like the others while ALSO being your best fit! The difference is the passion to sell! If you know us, you know it already!

organization_raw_address: beacon, new york, united states
organization_short_description:
Welcome to Reefer Madness, the most familiar and rebelliously iconic brand in the cannabis sphere. Originating as a 1930s propaganda film, today we stand as a proprietary eponym for anti-drug hysteria, and moralistic propaganda, satirizing and punching up at serious issues in a way that makes you smile and feel like part of a like-minded community of critical thinkers and free-spirits. We are steeped in irony and camp, a conversation starter, a historical nod, and a forward-looking brand in the evolving cannabis culture.

- Our ambition is to leverage the Reefer Madness brand's legacy as a satirical critique of anti-drug hysteria into an instantly recognizable branding and retail opportunity.
- We aim to tap into the massive total addressable cannabis market, turning this iconic brand into a valuable licensing opportunity for partners in the cannabis industry and beyond, including complementary consumer packaged goods (CPG) categories.
- We are committed to utilizing the elements of camp, satire, and irony inherent to the Reefer Madness franchise to connect with and speak to those who passionately oppose the ongoing drug war and today's propagandist movements that perpetuate similar harm.

Partnering with Reefer Madness means aligning with a compelling and culturally influential brand. We provide a unique branding and retail opportunity, appealing to cannabis enthusiasts as well as those who appreciate the art, satire, and social commentary.

To explore collaborations or licensing opportunities, send us a message!

From casual looks to special occasion outfits, find high-quality, trendy pieces that blend comfort with elegance. Shop exclusive designs and vibrant prints that express your
organization_short_description:
Pinkyotto was established in 2005, and since then has exploded onto the fashion scene with six store locations, five of which are situated in the trendiest parts of New York City — including the East Village, Nolita, West Village, Flatiron, and Williamsburg — in addition to their location in Boston, prominently stationed on the famous shopper's mecca of Newbury Street.

Pinkyotto is the brainchild of Ryo Liu, a former model and MFA graduate from Pratt Institute, and Peter Hsia who hails from the fast-paced world of finance and graduated from NYU's Stern School of Business. Noticing a void for edgy, yet elegant fashion at an affordable price point, presented by way of knowledgeable and approachable sales associates, Ryo envisioned a fun-filled, charming place for stylish girls to turn to for all of their wardrobe necessities.

Ryo's "a-ha!" moment arose when she decided that Pinkyotto would become a recreation of her best friend's closet; a space filled with a selection of distinct and uniquely cut, vintage-inspired pieces with bold, artistic prints. Peter makes sure these fashions of fancy don't break the bank. Together, they make Pinkyotto an attainable luxury.

A dichotomous edit, Pinkyotto offers a little something for everyone—from ultra-feminine daytime wear to pieces fit for the most daring of night vixens. Pinkyotto has rapidly become a favorite go-to destination for both the uptown and downtown girl to get her fashion fix. As a result, there has been a clamoring for more Pinkyotto.

organization_short_description:
ClimbTech: The Anchoring Innovators for Fall Protection, Rope Access, Confined Space, Work-at-Height, Mining, Rescue, Rock Climbing and More.

Twenty-five years ago, two avid rock climbers with a knack for invention saw a need for advancement in climbing equipment technology. They put their heads together and began to make their designs a reality.

In 1998, these climbers realized that their spring-loaded anchors were in demand well beyond the mountains. Much larger fields with extensive safety concerns such as the construction, industrial, military and mining industries were plagued by outdated, heavy, and cumbersome equipment. Thus, ClimbTech was founded.

Today, ClimbTech's innovative anchor solutions have achieved a global reputation for dependability. And with contractors and climbers alike sharing success stories made possible by ClimbTech products, ClimbTech continues to grow. organization_short_description:
Cockpit USA is a made in the USA fashion brand, built on the firm foundations of an affinity for leather, aviation & an all-American heritage since 1975.

Mission
In today's society where our clothes often reflect our individuality, we should cherish the ability to stand apart from the crowd in the CockpitTM USA collection. Our passion is to preserve the heritage of American life styles and take pride in reminiscing about the classic iconic eras of American fashion.

Description
From the Founders of Avirex LTD. was born Cockpit USA. The first to bring Vintage and contemporary Aviation/ Military inspired apparel back into fashion starting in the mid 1970's. It has evolved from military influence to include classic american heritage styles and symbolize the rugged yet stylish fashions of American Culture. Since that time there have been many imitators but there is only one original. Working closely with the USAF we helped bring back the A-2 Flight Jacket into military use in 1987, have supplied Navy, Marine, and Coast Guard Units, as well as many foreign Militaries. We have been fan favorites of Civilian Pilots, Air Show Performers, Military Pilots, Movie Stars, Sports Stars, and the function and fashion conscious who look for high quality outerwear, predominantly made in the USA. We strive to produce a quality garment that can last years and be passed down generations.

organization_short_description:
A Fish Story…

1917 – As America was at war and food supplies rationed, seafood loving Seattleites were faced with a fish shortage of epic proportions. Enterprising businessmen, hoping to make a large profit on the meager supply, took advantage of the situation by inflating prices well beyond what average shoppers could afford. Citizens were outraged. Sensing a crisis, then Washington State Governor Ernest Lister stepped in, insisting on a plan to guarantee that a state controlled supply of fish be delivered by the City of Seattle to consumers at the lowest possible price. He asked that the Fisheries Commission turn over to the Seattle city government dead hatchery salmon that were killed for their eggs and sperm. On January 14, 1917, an emergency ordinance was introduced to the Seattle City Council by Washington State Fish Commissioner L.H. Darwin requesting that money be set aside from the general budget to establish, maintain and operate a city owned fish market.

On January 25th 1918, the Municipal Fish Market opened in one of the original stalls on Pike Place. Immediately, throngs of consumers swooped down on the business, buying their three and half pound limit of fish and oysters at a third of the previous cost. In fact, that first day over 1,391 pounds of salmon alone were sold to hungry Seattleites. The Municipal Fish Market was a hit!

In 1923, the city elected to get out of the fish business and leased the market to a private owner. Rechristened City Fish, Seattle's original seafood company stood at the entrance to Pike Place Market, offering a full line of fresh seafood at a fair price, now direct from the fisherman to the consumer.

One hundred years later, Seattle's original seafood company, City Fish Seafood Market, still stands in its original location in the heart of the Pike Place Market. Come by, take a photo and shop our wide selection of fisherman-direct fresh seafood at fair prices.

name: Jon Martino
organization_raw_address: 1684 N. Belcher Rd, Clearwater, FL 33765, US
organization_seo_description: Fuse Lenses has the best new replacement lenses for your favorite name brand sunglasses. Polarized, prescription, color enhancing, and custom lenses available. Easy to install yourself. Made in the USA. Free U.S. shipping on orders over $55
organization_short_description:
Over a decade ago, we kicked off this adventure in sunny Clearwater, FL with a local hero - Carlos, a firefighter whose sunglasses were not just an accessory, but a piece of his identity that were with him for every fire he battled, trail he conquered, and waters he explored.  
 
Frustrated with expensive and wasteful decisions every time his favorite shades scratched, he was the first to ask co-founders, Brandon Dill and Jon Martino, "Can't I just replace the lenses in my sunglasses?" 

At the time, they already had extensive experience working in prescription optical labs and quickly dove into the world of "plano" lens technology. And it would never be the same.  
 
At the start, only low-quality, thin, and wavy lenses were available, what most would consider "gas station lenses." They set out, working alongside some of the top lens manufacturers to create something better. 
 
Today, every pair of Fuse Lenses is made of "better-than-brand-name," shatterproof Polycarbonate that is 3x more durable and backed by a 60-day guarantee and lifetime warranty. Fuse Lenses is also the only place to get a true color-enhancing lens that is made for any brand name sunglasses. And it's not over yet.  

From the very beginning, every lens cut, new product introduced, and innovation made is driven by the voice of our customers, our "Fuse Squad." Fuse Lenses is not just a company, but a community driven by a collective desire to keep the things we love, and our adventures, alive.

name: Andy Yang
organization_raw_address: 313 N Birch St, Santa Ana, California 92701, US
organization_short_description:
Since its founding in 2014, Houseables, Inc. has been a steadily rising name in the world of online home and industrial goods. We sell various items for all parts of your home — whether it's cooking, cleaning, storage, or even vanity mirrors for your bedroom. Many of our items are simple in function, others are practically ingenious, but each and every one of them has a distinct purpose aimed at making your everyday life a little more convenient.

Internally, Houseables is a veritable melting pot of unique and hilarious individuals. Our massive workforce of fourteen people (plus a team of seven in China) may not sound like a lot, but we all perform many different functions for the company. We play to our strengths and we strive to learn as much as we can, improving our skill sets along the way. There are no weak links; just sharp-minded, very cool people from all walks of life with unique interests, passions, style, and personality. More often than not, laughter can be heard resonating throughout the walls of our office and warehouse spaces. It's a little contagious, really.

A lot of young start-ups might delve into the adage of "work hard, play hard," but we cannot think of another place that believes in that philosophy more than Houseables. The perks of working here are pretty solid. Weekends off, paid holidays off, birthdays off, flexible vacation time and sick days, and a generous health care package. We have monthly team outings, plenty of free meals and holiday potlucks. We love the holidays most of all and we love having any excuse to celebrate them.

Throughout the past few years, we've upgraded everything we sell, expanded our presence online into different countries, and expanded to a bigger location to better suit our needs. But our business model remains the same: we focus on developing loyalty with our awesome customers by offering the lowest prices possible on the highest quality items.

organization_short_description:
803-649-6236

Since our founding in 1937 our focus has remained on customer service. As a multi-generation family business, we strive to maintain and improve the service we provide our customers. The story of today's Master Pontiac Buick GMC began in 1926 when a young Walter Schlapp arrived in Augusta from Germany to take a job arranged for him by a U.S. citizen who spent his summers in Germany. The 20-yea...r-old Schlapp was a trained metal worker but gladly accepted the job with an ice and coal business to avoid a crushing economic depression in Germany.


William Schafer, Schlapp's best friend has also realized the seriousness of the German depression and joined Schlapp in the ice and coal business using his skills as a bookkeeper. Both men intended to return to Germany to remain; however, time and fate intervened and in 1930 the two best friends married sisters and honeymooned on an ocean liner - back to the U.S. and their old jobs at the ice and coal business in Augusta.

By implementing a Business Process Improvement (BPI) strategy we strive at identifying the operations or employee skills that can be improved to encourage smoother procedures, more efficient workflows and overall business growth.  

Document Management Solutions (DMS): is a system (based on computer programs in the case of the management of digital documents) used to track, manage and store documents and reduce paper. Most are capable of keeping a record of the various versions created and modified by different users (history tracking).

Managed Print Services (MPS): is a program that manage all aspects of your business printing devices, including printers, scanners, faxes and copiers. By optimizing these devices, businesses save money, produce less paper waste and increase efficiency.

organization_short_description:
The Fizz Boutique is Clemson's one-stop-shop for you to celebrate all of life's moments- big & small! From the perfect outfit to the perfect gift, we are here to make each moment unforgettable.

In December 2018 I graduated from Clemson University with a BA in Communication and a minor in Business Administration. Since high school, I have had a passion for boutiques and small chain retail. After managing Razzberry Fizz for several months, I knew that this is what I was made to do for a living. When the opportunity to own a boutique presented itself, the answer seemed so clear.. YES! But there are so many risks in owning a business. I've always been a risk taker, but never had to make a life decision of this magnitude. This meant dedicating myself and my life to this boutique, with no option to change my mind- as I frequently do. Prayers, tears, fear, but mostly excitement! I began to have a vision for this local spot and saw so much potential not only for the store but also in myself. On October 23, 2019, risk = taken. I am so excited to share this journey with y'all and can't wait for The Fizz Boutique to become a Clemson staple and your go-to hometown boutique.

organization_short_description:
Cockpit USA is a made in the USA fashion brand, built on the firm foundations of an affinity for leather, aviation & an all-American heritage since 1975.

Mission
In today's society where our clothes often reflect our individuality, we should cherish the ability to stand apart from the crowd in the CockpitTM USA collection. Our passion is to preserve the heritage of American life styles and take pride in reminiscing about the classic iconic eras of American fashion.

Description
From the Founders of Avirex LTD. was born Cockpit USA. The first to bring Vintage and contemporary Aviation/ Military inspired apparel back into fashion starting in the mid 1970's. It has evolved from military influence to include classic american heritage styles and symbolize the rugged yet stylish fashions of American Culture. Since that time there have been many imitators but there is only one original. Working closely with the USAF we helped bring back the A-2 Flight Jacket into military use in 1987, have supplied Navy, Marine, and Coast Guard Units, as well as many foreign Militaries. We have been fan favorites of Civilian Pilots, Air Show Performers, Military Pilots, Movie Stars, Sports Stars, and the function and fashion conscious who look for high quality outerwear, predominantly made in the USA. We strive to produce a quality garment that can last years and be passed down generations.

organization_short_description:
You have thought about choosing your wedding dress your whole life.  Maybe Mom and Sister are with you, perhaps Dad and Grandmom, too, and so are we. We get to share in one of the most incredibly special memories ever to be made. What an honor to be part of that.

We are a proud family-owned business who is here to stand by you during your entire wedding buying process.  We smile with you, we clap with you and we cry with you.

First allow us to help you find the perfect wedding dress.  Once you are perfectly situated with your wedding dress, we then start helping your bridesmaid and flower girl - it's a lot of fun!  Then it's the guy's turn.  With over 70 styles of tuxedos and suits, groom, groomsmen, dads and ring bearer will certainly find exactly what you want for your wedding day.

We have also received the couples' choice award by WeddingWire and Pick of the the Knot.

We are accredited by the Better Business Bureau and are proud to serve you with integrity and an A+ rating by the BBB.

Our family, employees and community are very important to us.  We partner with wonderful causes such as Wish Upon A Wedding, Angel Gowns, St. Jude's, and Cinderella's Closet. We donate to the theater, band, and music programs of local schools, partner in many senior year events, and sponsor school and community athletic associations. Giving back is very important to us in our business and personal lives. In September 2015, we moved Darianna Bridal & Tuxedo to a new, larger location.  The name Darianna is a combination of the names of our two daughters, Daria and Deanna.

We would be honored to be a part of your special day and memories, too.

Visit us in person or on line at https://www.dariannabridal.com/

You can also call or text us at 215-491-8500.

A large selection in all sizes from one of the best lingerie stores in the country, renowned for service, value and fitting expertise. Popular brands & the world’s top designers. organization_short_description:
Awards: 
2005 Best of Intima Special Recognition - Best Women's Care in North America
2012 Best of Intima Special Recognition - Best Destination Store in North America
2015 Best of Intima Awards, Best Reference Shop in North America
2017 - Nominated for Best of Intima Award
2018 - Nominated for Best of Intima Award
2019 - Best of Intima Awards: Best Lingerie Shop in the USA
2020 - Nominated for Best of Intima Award
2021 - Nominated for Best of Intima Award
2022 - Best of Intima Awards: Heritage Award

Top Choice Award 2016, 2017 - Best Lingerie Store in Austin


Petticoat Fair opened in 1964 on Guadalupe Street in Austin, TX. Owners Bob and Betty Andrews' concept was to provide service to all women in need of intimate apparel. As the business grew, Petticoat Fair moved to Highland Mall and eventually to Northcross Center, where it is located today. In 2022 Petticoat Fair opened a second location, formerly known as Loretta's Intimates in Plano, Texas.

The principles of bra fitting and customer service have remained the same since the store's opening: Every woman is treated with respect and given one-on-one attention to help her feel comfortable and confident in properly fitted undergarments. The techniques Betty learned in corsetiere school and other training courses are still used in the store today, which is now owned by their youngest son, Kirk Andrews.

organization_short_description:
Mehraban is a California-based luxury rug company specializing in new and antique rug collections that are all designed here in Los Angeles. For three generations, Mehraban has always put the poetry, mystery and artistry of rug weaving at the forefront of every new design innovation or antique acquisition.

Several collections debut annually, adding to the sophisticated offering by some of the city's top designers.

In their hand-selected antique rugs, you will find subtleties of culture, weave, tribal symbolism, materials and dyes. Versed in the subtleties of regional design, the staff explains the differences between weavings created near the mountains and those made close to the sea. Each of these details has a distinct impact on the materials, quality and fineness of Mehraban's antique rugs.

Mehraban pays extraordinary attention to their processes, which include hand washing, hand shearing, and other proprietary details, all of which play a critical part in the final product.

Retail Reworks partners with DTC brands and retailers to streamline their reverse logistics capabilities and guide them on their journey to becoming fully circular.  We do this in a variety of ways throughout our divisions.

Complete Returns Solutions powered by our proprietary R4 software
The R4 platform is an API-powered, end-to-end returns solution featuring real-time insights and a 360-degree view across your inventory lifecycle. 
Customized to meet your requirements, you can reduce transportation and shipping costs while sending fewer returns to the landfill. 

Our robust partner network offers seamless API connections between returns software providers and the R4 platform. The result? We deliver the data you need to make business decisions - across inventory, donations, destructions, and 3PL shipments

Next Life
Reduce environmental impact and boost your bottom line. From recycling to donation, and rework to destruction, our Next Life services help your brand adopt sustainable business practices and outsource full circular manufacturing processes to avoid the landfill and give your products a second life in the marketplace.

Another Life
Join the sustainable fashion movement, keeping more products out of the landfill and recapturing profits. We inspect, clean, repair, and finish all types of products to get them back into inventory fast.  We bring over 95% of returns sent here back to first quality.  

White Label by Retail Reworks
We help our re-commerce and 3PL partners achieve remarkable business growth by providing the full suite of reverse logistics, warehousing, and returns solutions, becoming the backbone of your on-the-ground operations. We provide the labor and warehouse to support your marketplace and growth.

We also offer:
Reverse Logistics Consulting
QC Corrections & Inspections
Value-Added Services

organization_seo_description: Sustainably crafted and health-conscious hair care and styling products that deliver on the promise of style.
organization_short_description:
At Highland, we believe in individuality and in self expression through style... But we came to the realization that the products we were using not only deteriorate your health as you use them, but they deteriorate the health of our ecosystems, too. 

So we resolved to create prestige products that deliver on the promise of style without compromising on our values of health and sustainability.

At first, this looked like us ordering bulk natural ingredients online and formulating our Glacial Clay Pomade on our Denver, CO apartment stovetop to sell to friends and family... Today, our products are produced with only the use of natural, earth-based ingredients in Los Angeles, California, have won international grooming awards, and are sold all over the country.

We're on a mission to create not only the best products on the market, but products that improve the health of your hair and scalp as you use them.

Watch the Highland Story here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T6NTnCgpgmQ&t=2s

The Scofield family had been fans of Carhartt workwear for years. In fact, we found we preferred Carhartt clothing every day, even if we weren't working in the yard, hiking, or doing any of the rough and tumble activities that Carhartt clothing is so great for. We just liked how it looked and felt. We discovered for ourselves that no other outdoor clothing brand beats the construction or durability of Carhartt clothes, either.

The decision to open a store to offer Carhartt clothing seemed like a natural choice. Our first brick and mortar Carhartt shop opened in Loveland, Colorado, in 1999.  Because we already carried the most extensive stock of great Carhartt clothing in our stores, it just made sense to make it available online. Now TheWorkwearStore.com is one of the top Carhartt clothing dealers, recognized in 2008 as a preferred online retailer by Carhartt itself! organization_short_description:
Mehraban is a California-based luxury rug company specializing in new and antique rug collections that are all designed here in Los Angeles. For three generations, Mehraban has always put the poetry, mystery and artistry of rug weaving at the forefront of every new design innovation or antique acquisition.

Several collections debut annually, adding to the sophisticated offering by some of the city's top designers.

In their hand-selected antique rugs, you will find subtleties of culture, weave, tribal symbolism, materials and dyes. Versed in the subtleties of regional design, the staff explains the differences between weavings created near the mountains and those made close to the sea. Each of these details has a distinct impact on the materials, quality and fineness of Mehraban's antique rugs.

Mehraban pays extraordinary attention to their processes, which include hand washing, hand shearing, and other proprietary details, all of which play a critical part in the final product.

organization_short_description:
Oliver's Candies was established in 1932 by Joseph Boyd Oliver. Mr. Oliver blanched peanuts in his home, then went out to stores and gas stations to sell his product. After experimenting with formulas, homemade recipes, long hours and hard work, he developed such now-famous products as Cashew Glaze and Hostess Squares.

Oliver's uses original family proven recipes, the very best ingredients, including real butter, cream, honey and other natural products. New owner and operator, Jeremy Day, comes from a family that has spent their lives selling and servicing vehicles in the Rocky Mountain West. Jeremy and his family chose Great Falls and are committed to the community and the people. 

The unique setting of Great Falls Subaru at the corner of 8th and Central is steeped in Montana auto history as the former home of Bennett Motors. The showroom that still stands on our lot was built in 1948 and is on the registry of National Historic Places. Bennett Motors was established more than 100 years ago, and Carroll Bennett started serving customers in 1915 when the automotive business was in its infancy. We're proud of our history and welcome the generations of loyal customers back to our downtown dealership.

organization_short_description:
CPR® Mağazaları - Cep Telefonu Tamirinden Çok Daha Fazlası
Her şeyden önce ve en önemlisi, biz sorun çözeriz. Yeterli ekipman ve teknik bilgi yeterliliğine sahip uzman kadro tarafından cihaz sorunları taranır, tespit edilir ve çözüme kavuşturulur. Akıllı telefonla beraber; bilgisayar, dizüstü bilgisayar, oyun konsolu, kamera, mp3 çalar ve diğer yeni nesil elektronik aygıt bakım onarım hizmeti verilir. 
1997'den beri büyüyen bir aileyiz
Amacımız hizmet verdiğimiz herkese kazanç sağlamaktır. 1997 yılında Orlando'daki ilk cep telefonu tamir atölyemizden bu yana muazzam bir şekilde büyüdük; ve bu süreçte yerel hizmete olan bağlılığımız değişmedi. Dünyanın dört bir yanındaki okullara, şirketlere ve tüketicilere onarım çözümleri sağlamaya devam ediyoruz.
Doğaya saygılıyız.  Dünyanın, daha iyi bir yer olmasına yardımcı olmak için doğayı seven ve saygı gösteren şirket olarak eski, kullanılmış pilleri ve parçaları geri dönüşümde kullanıyoruz.  Elektronik cihaz ve parçaların ömrünü uzatmak ve çöpe gitmesini engellemek için onları onarıyoruz. Bu uygulamalar, karbon ayak izimizi en aza indirmemizi sağlar ve doğa üzerinde olumlu etki bırakır.
Müşterilerimiz bizim için her şeydir; onların ihtiyaçlarına daha iyi yanıt verebilmek için sürekli olarak büyümek, işlemlerimizi ve tekniklerimizi geliştirmeyi hedefliyoruz. 6 Aylık garantimiz, müşterilerimizin gönlünün ferah olmasına ne kadar değer verdiğimizin bir örneğidir. Ayrıca, nitelikli onarım ve üstün hizmet anlayışımızın göstergesidir. Her gün müşterilerimiz, bize ne kadar mutlu ve iyi olduklarını söylemeye devam ediyor.

organization_short_description:
Mullybox: Making Golf Easier for Everyone

At Mullybox, we're dedicated to making golf accessible and enjoyable for golfers of all levels. Our mission is simple: Golf is hard, but we're here to make it easy.

Our Journey:
Mullybox began as a quarterly subscription box delivering curated golf products directly to your door. Each box is packed with high-quality gear, apparel, and training aids designed to enhance your game. We've grown to become a leading D2C brand, offering a wide range of innovative products tailored specifically for golfers.

Our Products:

Quarterly Subscription Box: Every three months, our subscribers receive a box filled with the latest golf essentials, from cutting-edge gadgets to stylish apparel.

Direct-to-Consumer (D2C) Golf Products: We offer an extensive line of products available for purchase directly through our online store, ensuring you have access to the best golf gear.

The Next Evolution - Greens Club:
Building on our success, we've launched Greens Club, an exclusive online community for golfers. Greens Club offers expert swing feedback, networking opportunities, and member-only discounts, all accessible from your phone.

Why Choose Mullybox?

Quality: Top brands and industry expertise.
Convenience: Easy access to the gear you need.
Community: A supportive community of golf lovers.

Join Us:
Mullybox is here to make your golfing experience better, simpler, and more enjoyable. Join us on our mission to make golf easy and discover the difference that quality products and a supportive community can make in your game.

Visit us at www.mullybox.com to learn more and become part of the Mullybox family today!

headline: OWNER at CopySmart
keywords: retail office equipment
name: Derek Manis
organization_raw_address: Unit 11/101 Kurrajong Avenue Mount Druitt, Sydney, New South Wales 2770, AU
organization_seo_description: Get advanced Photocopiers in Sydney, available for all budgets. Save your money on photocopier printer machine lease or rental. Tested and Inspected by Ex-Xerox Technicians. We can install homes and office printers within Sydney, or buyer can pick up.
organization_short_description:
The history of Copy Smart began when a friend who was a minister at an Anglican church asked me if I could help him source a cheap second hand photocopier. Knowing that I had worked with Fuji Xerox as a contractor for 5 years as a National Operations Manager, he could trust me to get the best possible deal on a copier for him. Well, I had left work with Fuji Xerox a few years earlier but I said that I would try to source one for him.

Unfortunately that took longer than he was able to wait, and he ended up purchasing an expensive second hand "analogue" Richo copier with very "high copy count" and a "long term contract" with a "high click charge" rate.

I hate it when people get ripped off. If someone tried to sell you a car, you would know what a reasonable make and price would be on that car, but when purchasing a second hand photocopier most people do not have the faintest idea. So either they overestimate the cost of a copier or they underestimate the cost of one.

WP specializes in wood and plastic fabrication and is known for custom millwork & casework, store fixtures, interiors, POP displays and cabinetry. MPC provides both acoustical products and materials nationally, as well as installation services through our national network. We also consult locally. https://www.mpcsilentwall.com/

name: Mehraban Rugs
organization_raw_address: 545 N La Cienega Blvd, Los Angeles, California 90048, US
organization_seo_description: Mehraban offers the finest collection of luxury rugs in the US. View our exclusive collections of Persian Rugs, Modern Rugs, Moroccan Rugs, Moroccan Rugs and Luxury Rugs. Best Rug Store in Los Angeles. Moroccan Rugs Los Angeles. Persian Rugs Los Angeles
organization_short_description:
Mehraban is a California-based luxury rug company specializing in new and antique rug collections that are all designed here in Los Angeles. For three generations, Mehraban has always put the poetry, mystery and artistry of rug weaving at the forefront of every new design innovation or antique acquisition.

Several collections debut annually, adding to the sophisticated offering by some of the city's top designers.

In their hand-selected antique rugs, you will find subtleties of culture, weave, tribal symbolism, materials and dyes. Versed in the subtleties of regional design, the staff explains the differences between weavings created near the mountains and those made close to the sea. Each of these details has a distinct impact on the materials, quality and fineness of Mehraban's antique rugs.

Mehraban pays extraordinary attention to their processes, which include hand washing, hand shearing, and other proprietary details, all of which play a critical part in the final product.

Mehraban is a California-based luxury rug company specializing in new and antique rug collections that are all designed here in Los Angeles. headline: Co-Founder
name: Nathan Hamood
organization_raw_address: 22016 Woodward Ave, Ferndale, Michigan 48220, US
organization_short_description:
When you can't find exactly what you want, sometimes you just have to dig in and create it yourself. In early 2016, that's precisely what we did. Nate began putting together small batches of natural ingredients to create an easy-to-use, water-based product that had incredible hold, with a natural feel and pliable texture – something that didn't really exist at the time. We'd love to say our first batch was flawless, and we launched our business the next day, but that's just not how life works. 

After the first few batches, it seemed as though Nate was better at making candles than he was at producing pomade … but he stuck with it. And a few months later, our Original Pomade was born. We had finally pioneered a new pomade that was everything we had been looking for. Once Nate's extensive research and formulating started to show promise, Christian hopped on board, and we made the jump from a small passion project to a full-fledged business. And in August of 2016, we released our first production batch of Ace High Original Pomade to the public.
In the early days, finding time for production was difficult, but we always had a blast because our passion for our products pushed us to stay motivated. Oftentimes, we would have to work during the wee hours of the night to utilize the commercial kitchen of our coffee shop. Our methods were definitely not ideal, but eventually we perfected the process. And with the help of a modified crockpot and many sleepless nights in the kitchen of our coffee shop, we produced the first 25 official jars of Ace High Original Pomade.
Since launching our Original Pomade, we've developed a full Ace High product line that includes Pomade, Beard Balm, Tonic, Shampoo and Conditioner. We've moved past the crockpot to an actual production space in our own red brick building with a rad staff dedicated to production and manufacturing.

BIG RED SUN is a full service design studio specializing in sustainable, architectural landscapes for residential and commercial spaces. Well known for its modern and timeless landscape magic, it's pairing of botanical, earth and marine elements in vertical, standing and hanging gardens, BIG RED SUN offers many settings for it's clientele.

Created by owner and designer Selena Souders in 1994, BIG RED SUN is located in Austin, Texas and Venice, California. BIG RED SUN offers landscape and garden design services; interior and exterior botanical art commissions; wedding/special event floral & plant décor, a boutique nursery and garden shop; and venues available for special events.

Renowned for it's use of restorative, native, and naturalized plantings combined with innovative vessels and hardscapes, BIG RED SUN has been featured in Metropolitan Home, HOUSE & GARDEN, WIRED, Garden Design Magazine, Texas Monthly, Austin's hip Hotel San Jose, Rose Café, Fred Segal Santa Monica to name a few.  Also, BIG RED SUN has worked with top celebrities such as singer Shawn Colvin, Martha Stewart, Owen Wilson, Patricia Arquette, Matthew McConaughey and Brad Pitt and high profile events such as NRDC'S Annual Fundraiser, Texas Film Hall of Fame Fundraiser, Avatar Movie Earth Day Premiere Event and many more. 
 
BIG RED SUN has established itself as the go-to landscape visionary for the design-minded client.

The pair formed their alliance over a British puppy adopted by Davis while stationed in wartime England. After accomplishing a stateside transfer for the lucky pup, the two remained friends, joining forces in the pet food business. Davis passed away in the late ‘60s, but Cohen soldiered on with their enterprise through 1995, when the business was purchased by Barry Jacobson and his sons Adam and Ari, who run the business today.

 When the business was re-conceived in 1995, the large warehouse space which was home to the original Pet Pantry was converted into a more modern shopping experience and a new business model was born. 

 The success of the reformatted Greenwich location paved the way for additional locations in Rye, NY in 2006, Larchmont, NY, in 2010.  A fourth location in New Canaan, CT, opened in late 2012 along with another store in neighboring Wilton, CT. The options for a convenient local shopping experience have continued to grow with additional stores in Riverside, CT,  Scarsdale, NY and our 7th store located at 1876 Blackrock Turnpike in Fairfield, CT opened in the Summer of 2018. 

 As a local, family run business we understand the importance of giving back to the communities in which we operate. Over the years we have been extremely active in support of local and surrounding communities we serve by donating hundreds of thousands of dollars' worth of money, goods, and services.

organization_seo_description: Zane's Cycles is a New England bicycle store located in both Branford and Fairfield Connecticut, started by Christopher J. Zane in 1980. Offering a wide variety of Bikes, Bike Accessories, Bike Fit
organization_short_description:
Zane's Cycles is a New England bicycle store located in Branford, Connecticut, started by Christopher J. Zane in 1980, at the age of 16. Since then, the store has grown from a local bicycle and hobby shop, to the largest P&I (Premiums and Incentives) distributor of bicycles in the United States.

The story of Zane's growth from small shop owner to major distributor found its way into several major business publications and college courses on marketing. Inc. and Fortune magazines both wrote positively of his aggressive local strategies, labeling them in some cases as "guerrilla marketing". An example was his tactic of purchasing competitor's phone numbers after putting them out of business.

In another quite opposite strategy, his focus on establishing a bond with the customer through simple gestures -- like selling children's helmets at dealer cost, and offering lifetime guarantees -- was a topic in an article by the Harvard Business Review.

organization_seo_description: Never worry about finding a clean, working changing station again. Paperclip's diaper bag changing stations are the solution for any parents on the go.
organization_short_description:
Welcome to Paperclip. Where innovation, sustainability and the family experience form the three pillars of everything we've believed in since 2017. 

OUR VISION
Take our groundbreaking diaper bags, for example. We weren't going to just go out there and make more of the same. Not a chance. From its iconic, patented and integrated changing station to its luxury design, Paperclip bags are a true game changer that both moms and dads can throw over their shoulders with confidence. But we didn't stop there.

The health and well-being of our planet is important to us, and we've taught our children about the impact of sustainability at an early age. And we're doing that by example. That's why all our products are made using recycled plastics from our oceans and rivers, fields and beaches. We're proud of the small part we play in making the planet a cleaner place for all our children, ours and yours. 

All this leads to the most important part of all - a better family experience. When parents are filled with confidence, have fewer things to worry about when it comes to the care of their children, and feel good about the product choices they make, they can spend more time enjoying the precious moments with their family. 

And we're just getting started. In 2024 you'll see new product innovations like sustainably made high chairs, feeding products that truly stimulate a child's five senses, and a brand-new line of diaper bags that will change the game all over again.

organization_seo_description: Super Smalls is a feel good accessories brand that celebrates the sparkle in all of us. At Super Smalls, we prioritize play, we love to laugh and we add a little umph to the everyday!
organization_short_description:
Super Smalls is inspired by the joy of the extravagant and the whimsical. We take our inspiration from glitzy, grown up stuff— decadent fine jewelry and bold fashion—and translate that for a child's eye. 

Super Smalls is intended for children ages 3 to 12 and anyone young at heart (but old enough to know not to put an earring in their mouth!)

Super Smalls accessories are designed and packaged to look and feel like gifts. A Super Smalls box is a special thing to receive: a treat, a treasure, an easy indulgence, and a pathway to fun.

An experienced leader in the fashion and accessories industry, Maria Dueñas Jacobs founded Super Smalls to combine her love for refined, beautiful and ornate objects with her passion for all things fun and kid-centric.

With three (super) small daughters, Maria's family home is a headquarters of make believe, dress up and fearless fun. Super Smalls was born out of the idea that no matter how many beads and kids jewelry her daughters were given, they always wanted to play with mom's jewelry instead.

Super Smalls encourages imagination and play for any child who enjoys a little extra sparkle.

organization_short_description:
In early April of 2015, the Louis family all sat down and prayed that the Lord would reveal a name for the company.... something with a true meaning. In just a few short weeks 4 Warriors Hydro Excavating was formed and up an running. 4 Warriors means "​ Warriors of Christ."​ 

Our goal as a Christian, family owned company is to not only make an impact on the industry but also on people's lives. At the end of the day we want our family to take care of your family. We've been blessed with some of the best operators and techs in the industry and also top of the line equipment. 4 Warriors Hydro Excavating is not only the most reliable and safest but also the most cost efficient in the industry. The key to success in this business is to put to a smile on every customers face and that's exactly what we aim to do.

4 Warriors is committed to exceeding our client's highest expectations, fully understanding timelines, safety and of course your price budget. 4 Warriors has advanced safety training that is required to work refineries, substations, and even nuclear facilities. The operators at 4 Warriors have been in the industry for more then 6 years with extensive training and have been involved in some of the largest projects in Texas. The industrial training allows us to really "show up"​ on civil projects and often be ahead of the curve.  Our full time HSE director manages our extensive site specific trainings, TWIC certifications, OQ certification, drug testing, and JSA procedures.   Bottom line, 4 Warriors is the best at what they do!

name: Paige Sandilands
organization_raw_address: tacoma, washington, united states
organization_seo_description: E I T H E R / O R is a small footwear brand dedicated to Ethical Sourcing, Fair Wages. We are obsessed with making the perfect everyday shoe. We partner with small workshops making sustainably sourced leather shoes with a quality absent in most modern footwear. Meet your new favorite pair.
organization_short_description:
E I T H E R / O R is just three people, working together to provide the best quality shoes directly to you. Selling direct-to-consumer gives us more freedom to run our business ethically. We employ a social cooperative to weave custom textiles, use the best quality vegetable-tanned leathers, pay beyond fair wages, and offset our shipping carbon footprint. We also use post-consumer, plastic-free packaging. Selling direct also means you save the traditional retail markup!

E I T H E R / O R is committed to sustainable sourcing, ethical manufacturing, and being a force for good in a changing world. Looking towards a brighter future, we are committed to staying true to ourselves and true to the ethical brand we are creating. Stay tuned!
-

We believe transparency is the first step to real change in the fashion industry. Companies should be held accountable for the conditions under which their products are made, and consumers should have the power to support brands based on their values. On each of our production partner pages, we provide details on fair wages, material sourcing, supplier information, and packaging. We are continually striving to be more transparent and faithfully tell the story of each pair that we produce.

We believe in buying fewer, better quality items that will age beautifully and preserve our environment. Our commitment is to produce product that is classic, comfortable, and the highest quality craftsmanship.

We are environmentally and socially conscious people. We are always striving to find ways to reduce waste in our supply chain through clean sourcing, mindful sampling, and small-scale production.

name: Nick Jensen

organization_seo_description: Official site: Fast, free standard shipping when you spend $50*. Lifetime Creations is home to hundreds of personalized gifts including custom wedding gifts, custom bar mirrors, personalized bridesmaid and groomsmen gifts, and other gifts for holidays and religious occasions. We offer fast turnaround and quick shipping. Create the perfect gift with Lifetime Creations. *See site for details.
organization_short_description:
Hi, we're Lifetime Creations. We're guessing you want to know more about us!

What we do
We design and decorate personalized gifts for life's happy moments, and ship quickly to customers across the US (most gifts are out our door within 2 business days). So whether you need the perfect gift for your mom on Mother's Day or something unique for your entire wedding party, we've got you covered. We also work with companies and brands who need gifts and promotional items with their custom logos.  

How we do it
Our gifts are all designed and decorated by our team with laser engraving, embroidery, or sublimation. Every single gift we ship is inspected by two of our team members to ensure we meet the highest quality standards. Our general rule of thumb: If you wouldn't be proud to give the gift to an important person in your life, it doesn't pass our quality inspection. We prioritize great customer service (be sure to Google us and our reviews) so you can be assured you'll get your questions answered or help if needed.

Where we are
We're based out of Merrillville, Indiana, about 45 minutes outside of Chicago.

Who we are
In 2007, Lifetime Creations officially got its start when Nick and his mom, Pat, purchased our original laser engraver. Over the next few years, Nick worked on the business part-time doing lots of custom projects and craft shows.

After Nick and Stephanie got engaged and started planning their own wedding in 2011, they realized there was a need for high quality, personalized wedding gifts and they launched our Etsy shop. They continued to do craft shows while our ecommerce business grew.

A few years later, Stephanie joined the business full time and we shortly hired our first part-time employee.

Fast forward to today, and we have a diverse team who runs all aspects of the business including several laser engravers, embroidery machines, and sublimation presses. We ship to all 50 states and have customers on Etsy, Amazon, and lifetimecreations.net.

organization_short_description:
After over 10 years in the jewelry business, each piece of Nina Berenato's collection still touches the designer's hands. From her humble beginnings as a metalsmith's apprentice in Brooklyn to gracing the pages of Vogue, W, Cosmopolitan, MTV and outfitting fashion-forward celebrities like Beyoncé, Alicia Keys, Lena Dunham, FKA Twigs and Lizzo, it's obvious that Nina walks through life with her eyes open, bringing a one of a kind vision to each design.

A large part of Nina Berenato's brand identity rests on the designer's goal to use her gift for design to make all women feel powerful, beautiful and capable of anything. Each piece is cast using 100% recycled metal, finished in the highest quality 14k gold plating, and set with stones that are sourced and mined ethically.

In 2018 Nina opened her flagship store now at 3200 Palm Way #152 at Domain NORTHSIDE where she produces her namesake collection, teaches jewelry making classes and leads her team of 5 incredible Austin women.

In 2019 Nina began a sustainability initiative that resulted in Nina Berenato Jewelry received Austin's highest honor from the City's Office of Sustainability - Green Business Leader Platinum.

In 2020 Nina created The Jewelry Academy, an online masterclass. A space where she can share her signature business strategies while helping emerging and seasoned jewelry designers everywhere.

organization_short_description:
Astro Gallery of Gems, one of the most prestigious gem and mineral galleries in the world, is prominently located on Fifth Avenue in New York City. The gallery boasts an impressive 10,000-square-foot showroom filled with extraordinary specimens, ranging from rare gems and minerals to fossils and high-end jewelry. Since 1961, Astro Gallery has been a premier destination for collectors, interior designers, and natural history enthusiasts alike. The gallery is renowned for offering museum-quality specimens, making it a leading source for both novice collectors and seasoned connoisseurs.

Astro Gallery's long-standing reputation is built on its dedication to curating the finest natural treasures. Over the decades, it has attracted high-profile clients such as Salvador Dalí, John Lennon, and Shirley MacLaine, further solidifying its place as a global authority in the gem and mineral industry. Visitors can explore a diverse array of specimens, including intricately designed gemstone jewelry, massive amethyst geodes, and unique fossils, each carefully selected for its rarity, beauty, and natural significance.

In recent years, Astro Gallery has expanded beyond its flagship Fifth Avenue location, opening additional galleries in Southampton, NY, and Meridian, Idaho. These new locations allow more collectors and enthusiasts to experience Astro Gallery's unparalleled collection and expertise. Each location is designed to provide an immersive experience, offering visitors the chance to explore Earth's natural wonders in a luxurious setting.

The gallery's commitment to showcasing nature's most exceptional creations is reflected in every detail, from the exquisite curation of minerals and gems to the exceptional service provided by its knowledgeable staff. Whether you are looking for a unique addition to your personal collection or a one-of-a-kind piece to elevate your living space, Astro Gallery offers an unparalleled experience.

organization_short_description: In June of 1940 Smokers' Haven was opened by its founder Joseph Zieve, his wife Ina, and his brother in-law Sid Ritter.  Joe and Sid were pioneers in the Retail market of pipes and tobaccos, and established a real Specialty Tobacco shop.  From 1940 until the late 1970's, Smokers' Haven was one of the largest and most distinguished Pipe and Tobacco shops in the world with an inventory of over 10,000 English pipes and a range of some of the best Pipe Tobacco Blends.  Joe and Sid would take frequent trips to England to develop new tobacco blends and new shapes for GBD pipes so they could offer unique and quality products for their customer base which numbered over 60,000.  In the late 1970's and early 1980's, the pipe market started to dwindle and many of the pipe and tobacco suppliers discontinued their products.  In 1983, Joe Zieve retired and sold Smokers' Haven.  The 2nd owner did not adapt to the market, and Smokers' Haven almost disappeared.  In 1987, my father Arvind Chheda, purchased Smokers' Haven and rescued it from demise.  Throughout the late 1980's and 1990's Cigars were the primary focus for Smokers' Haven.  In 1999, I was passed the torch, and  I have taken an interest in Pipes, and the methods in which Joseph Zieve serviced his customers.  From 2000 to present, Smokers' Haven has re-introduced the Specialty Products it was known for, and I hope to create a similar experience for our customers that Smokers' Haven did in the past.

name: Karen Macdonald-Basile

organization_seo_description: Wrapped in Love sells easy-to-wear tops post-mastectomy tops for everyday wear, comfortable recovery clothing for cancer patients and chemo hats for hair loss.
organization_short_description:
Like many stories in our lives, the Wrapped in Love story started with an illness.  

Our founder Karen's Mom had become very ill from cancer and pulmonary fibrosis. It was Christmas Eve and Karen's mom told her she no longer wanted to receive visitors as she felt she looked too bad in her state of illness. It broke Karen's heart to see how her mother had lost her dignity.  Karen decided that she was going to make her feel special and pretty on Christmas day.  She made her a wrap that could go over her hospital gown and put a pretty flower pin on it (she loved flowers and gardening).  Karen put a little bit of lipstick on her and gave her some rosy cheeks, and Karen saw her mother's familiar smile come back.  

That day inspired Karen for the rest of her life. Karen saw that helping someone feel and look special despite their illness could really make an impact on a patient's outlook and dignity.  That day Karen was inspired to create Wrapped in Love, a clothing and accessory line for women with cancer and other illnesses, to provide them with comfort, style and dignity, despite illness.

Behind every Wrapped in Love creation is a whole lot of care and core values that we never compromise on.

~Having cancer doesn't mean giving up your sense of style. 
~Chemo clothes should be designed with the patient in mind — but still be practical for healthcare workers.
~Made in the USA with love because you deserve the best.

Wrapped in Love has been featured in/on:
WWD (Women's Wear Daily), D Magazine, Fox 2 Detroit, Macomb Daily, Hour Detroit, Seen Magazine, Suncoast FYI, Macomb Now magazine, WJR radio, WWJ radio, Florine Mark's  Remarkable Woman show, WXYZ TV, WDIV TV,  Fox 2 Detroit, WFTS TV Tampa, WDVM TV Washington DC, WGVU radio, FOX/CBS Jacksonville, WWSB ABC7 Suncoast View, CBS San Diego.
